Update: 7/6/19: Keeping 4/5 stars but got to sit in the dining area. Probably the smallest dining area I've ever been in (two people would have issues walking next to each other).  The same area has restrooms (need key) and fountain drinks (also available in the front). If you need to access beverages, people sitting might need to move. The store arrangement is a bit bizarre; you can tell the front of the store used to be the food prep area and is presently unused space. They should remove the old counter there and make it the customer dining area while converting the existing elven dining area for staff.  Original review:  Has been consistently good and barely ever a line (like never really). Didn't notice there was a seating area in the rear as it's very nondescript. They're probably the fastest Subway I've been to.  However, one day the AC wasn't working and it was hotter than two hells in there. I hope that never happens again because it was pretty awful on the customer's side - I can't imagine what it's like behind the counter when that (hopefully rarely) happens.

This subway is just okay.  If you are spending the day in the courthouse, Subway is the most economical way to grab a bite.  The location is hit or miss. Sometimes the line is too long to bother entering. Other times no one is inside.  The employees are polite without being that outgoing or warm.  They seem automated.  There aren't any "frills" that this location.  The location is downtown and sometimes unusual characters hang around the entrance.  My veggie delight was yummy.
